chunk_content: In addition, all biological siblings of the index child should be offered HIV testing services. In this way, provision of index testing services is non-directional, whereby we are trying to follow transmission of the disease, and every newly identified positive becomes a subsequent index client from whom to elicit contacts. While testing the contacts of an index client may occur in mobile, VCT, or other community testing venue, this testing should be reported under HTS_INDEX. That is, if an individual could be reported under both HTS_INDEX and another HTS_TST modality, that individual should only be reported once under HTS_INDEX. Again, the index modality under HTS_TST will auto-populate from HTS_INDEX (see HTS_INDEX reference sheet for more information). B. Mobile: Testing in ad hoc mobile or temporary testing locations, such as community centers, schools, workplaces, and includes testing in mobile unit such as tents and vans.
